						<div class="postbody">31 is the last bank, and yeah before you replied I changed it to an actual entry point for that bank, and it seems to work in FCEUX. But FCEUX doesn't open in other emulators. And yeah, I guess it could be taken out, but 16 bytes is an okay header size for me, nice and "round, I think I'll just keep it in all banks *just in case* the MMC1 didn't take the read and then the boot code could run again if it fails.
<br />
<br />Yep, the 9F in bank 0 is $80, $81 in bank 1, etc. And yeah, 8KB sized banks is something I didn't take account for, then that means not needing it in all banks, so that should be $8F in the last bank and I need to change my code later for that.
<br />
<br />
<br />Also, not that I'm relying on it for something, but is the reset state of the CPU the same as the cold boot state? Or would A,X,Y just all be unchanged?</div>

