					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Only bit 0 ($01) and bit 7 ($80) of the value written to $8000-$FFFF are ever used. If bit 7 is true, all other bits are <em>ignored.</em> So $9F, $81, and $8F all have the same effect.
<br />
<br />You say having the actual entry point in the JMP fails in other emulators. What does it do if you step through it in Nintendulator?</div>

